1
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:07,199
<i>Deborah?</i>

2
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,325
- Where you been?
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry, T.

3
00:01:09,435 --> 00:01:11,335
- Are you cheating on me?
- No, no! I'm not cheating on you.

4
00:01:11,437 --> 00:01:13,928
- What...
- Stop it! What are you doing?

5
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:16,031
- T! Stop it!
- You ain't leaving me!

6
00:01:16,142 --> 00:01:19,077
- Who is it?
- Nobody! It's you! I hate you!

7
00:01:19,178 --> 00:01:22,204
T. Ray, just let me go!

8
00:01:22,315 --> 00:01:25,341
No!

9
00:01:25,451 --> 00:01:28,007
<i>T. Ray, damn it!
Get off me!</i>

10
00:01:28,187 --> 00:01:29,714
Lily!

11
00:01:37,697 --> 00:01:41,064
<i>I killed my mother when I was four years old.</i>

12
00:01:41,167 --> 00:01:43,863
<i>That's what I knew about myself.</i>

13
00:01:43,970 --> 00:01:46,837
<i>She was all I wanted,</i>
<i>and I took her away.</i>

14
00:01:48,141 --> 00:01:50,041
<i>Nothin' else much mattered.</i>

15
00:02:38,457 --> 00:02:39,924
- T. Ray!
- What?

16
00:02:40,026 --> 00:02:42,187
There's bees in my room!
Hundreds of' em! You've gotta see!

17
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:44,786
- What is it? Jesus Christ, Lily.
- They're in my room! Come see.

18
00:02:44,897 --> 00:02:46,865
What?

19
00:02:57,944 --> 00:02:59,844
Goddamn it, Lily.
This ain't funny.

20
00:02:59,946 --> 00:03:02,346
But they were here.
They were flyin' everywhere.

21
00:03:02,448 --> 00:03:04,814
You wake me again,
I'm gonna get out the grits.

22
00:03:04,917 --> 00:03:06,885
You hear me?

23
00:03:09,755 --> 00:03:11,723
<i>Goddamn it.</i>

24
00:03:24,203 --> 00:03:26,763
<i>The bees came the summer of'64...</i>

25
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:31,742
<i>The summer I turned 14 and my whole life</i>
<i>went spinnin' off into a whole new orbit.</i>

26
00:03:31,844 --> 00:03:35,644
<i>Lookin' back on it,</i>
<i>I wanna say they were sent to me.</i>

27
00:03:35,748 --> 00:03:40,208
<i>I wanna say they showed up like</i>
<i>the Angel Gabriel appearing to the Virgin Mary.</i>

28
00:03:40,319 --> 00:03:42,583
<i>I know it's forward to compare</i>
<i>my small life to hers...</i>

29
00:03:44,024 --> 00:03:47,983
<i>but I have good reason</i>
<i>to believe she wouldn't mind.</i>

30
00:04:16,090 --> 00:04:19,582
So, um, my birthday is tomorrow.

31
00:04:21,996 --> 00:04:24,590
Most girls want...

32
00:04:24,698 --> 00:04:29,726
one of them little silver charm bracelets
they have down at the mercantile.

33
00:04:29,837 --> 00:04:33,432
Think I'm the only girl in junior high
doesn't have one.

34
00:04:37,111 --> 00:04:40,638
But I was just thinking you could tell me
about my mother instead.

35
00:04:40,748 --> 00:04:44,650
<i>All you ever said is she's from Virginia</i>
<i>and she's an only child like I am.</i>

36
00:04:44,752 --> 00:04:46,982
<i>I don't even know what</i>
<i>her favorite food was...</i>

37
00:04:47,087 --> 00:04:50,716
<i>and what she liked</i>
<i>to do and...nothin;</i>

38
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:02,193
- You wanna know about your mama?
- Yeah.

39
00:05:03,304 --> 00:05:06,273
Mm-hmm.

40
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:09,399
She used to spend hours
lurin' roaches and whatnot...

41
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:12,206
out of the house with graham crackers
and marshmallows.

42
00:05:13,247 --> 00:05:15,909
Swear to God.

43
00:05:22,022 --> 00:05:24,013
She was a lunatic about savin' bugs.

44
00:05:39,106 --> 00:05:40,300
Here you go.

45
00:05:50,710 --> 00:05:54,669
<i>Hey, Lily! Nice ass!</i>

46
00:05:54,781 --> 00:05:56,749
Oh!

47
00:06:05,625 --> 00:06:07,593
Gotcha.

48
00:06:10,563 --> 00:06:14,294
Rosaleen.
Look at this thing fight.

49
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:17,426
- What you doin' with that?
- Catching bees to show T. Ray.

50
00:06:17,537 --> 00:06:19,437
He thinks I'm making it up.

51
00:06:19,539 --> 00:06:22,201
Get yourself stung,
don't come cryin' to me.

52
00:06:22,308 --> 00:06:25,471
- Come fix this.
- For the future...

53
00:06:25,578 --> 00:06:27,159
What'd they do?
Drop the atom bomb or somethin'?

54
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,741
Hush.

55
00:06:28,848 --> 00:06:33,046
It does say that there are those
who are equal before God...

56
00:06:33,152 --> 00:06:36,451
shall now also be equal
in the polling booths...

57
00:06:36,556 --> 00:06:38,888
in the classrooms,
in the factories...

58
00:06:38,992 --> 00:06:40,641
and in hotels and restaurants
and movie theaters...

59
00:06:40,642 --> 00:06:42,291
Holy shit.

60
00:06:42,395 --> 00:06:44,329
And other places that provide
service to the public.

61
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:46,955
Today, July the 2nd, 1964...

62
00:06:47,066 --> 00:06:49,694
President Johnson signed
the Civil Rights bill into law.

63
00:07:09,322 --> 00:07:12,257
Fifteen, 16, 17, 18...

64
00:07:12,358 --> 00:07:15,486
19, 20, 21, 22.

65
00:08:31,070 --> 00:08:33,868
<i>When's my hair gonna</i>
<i>look like yours?</i>

66
00:08:35,642 --> 00:08:39,669
I bet mine used to drive you crazy the way
it goes off in 11 wrong directions.

67
00:08:41,414 --> 00:08:45,248
I bet you used to brush it a hundred times a day
just to get it to lay down.

68
00:08:47,387 --> 00:08:49,855
I bet you did.

69
00:08:50,923 --> 00:08:54,882
<i> Lily!</i>

70
00:08:54,994 --> 00:08:56,962
<i>Lily!</i>

71
00:08:58,631 --> 00:09:00,599
<i>Lily!</i>

72
00:09:05,705 --> 00:09:07,935
- Who you out here with?
- What?

73
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:11,602
- Who's out there?
- Nobody. There's no one here but me. It's just me.

74
00:09:11,711 --> 00:09:13,645
Get up from there.

75
00:09:18,985 --> 00:09:21,351
Get in here.

76
00:09:21,454 --> 00:09:25,618
No! You think you're grown? Huh?

77
00:09:26,826 --> 00:09:29,818
Out there doing God knows what.

78
00:09:29,929 --> 00:09:33,160
You'll get yourself pregnant
and then what? Huh?

79
00:09:33,266 --> 00:09:35,291
Huh?

80
00:10:39,332 --> 00:10:41,300
You can go.

81
00:10:51,944 --> 00:10:54,879
Mornin'.

82
00:10:54,981 --> 00:10:57,609
How long your dad
keep you on these grits?

83
00:10:57,717 --> 00:10:59,685
Hour.

84
00:11:03,756 --> 00:11:05,747
Look at ya.

85
00:11:08,227 --> 00:11:10,354
Happy birthday.

86
00:11:11,664 --> 00:11:13,564
I didn't know you made me a cake.

87
00:11:13,666 --> 00:11:15,600
Of course I did.
It's your birthday.

88
00:11:15,701 --> 00:11:17,931
- How big a piece you want?
- Real big.

89
00:11:23,276 --> 00:11:25,676
You should be in the stand already.

90
00:11:25,778 --> 00:11:28,008
It's a big peach day.

91
00:11:32,185 --> 00:11:35,154
- Takin' her to town with me.
- What for?

92
00:11:35,254 --> 00:11:39,418
She needs a training bra.
She gots to get measured.

93
00:11:43,529 --> 00:11:45,520
How much something like that cost?

94
00:12:01,551 --> 00:12:03,815
Happy birthday.

95
00:12:10,927 --> 00:12:12,895
So what's in town anyway?

96
00:12:14,431 --> 00:12:17,025
I'm registerin' to vote.

97
00:12:17,134 --> 00:12:21,764
Rosaleen, news said a colored man in Mississippi
was killed for doing that.

98
00:12:22,906 --> 00:12:25,067
Good thing we ain't
in Mississippi then.

99
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:33,474
I saw you scribblin' one of your stories
in the stand yesterday.

100
00:12:34,751 --> 00:12:36,776
Go on. Tell it.

101
00:12:36,887 --> 00:12:39,151
All right.

102
00:12:39,256 --> 00:12:41,315
So The Supremes,
they're heading down Highway 4...

103
00:12:41,424 --> 00:12:43,915
because they're going to Charleston
for a real big concert.

104
00:12:44,027 --> 00:12:45,927
But suddenly, their back tire blows up...

105
00:12:46,029 --> 00:12:48,259
and they go skiddin' across the road
and into a ditch.

106
00:12:48,365 --> 00:12:51,425
So then two are saying
that Diana's burnin' the peach cobbler.

107
00:12:51,535 --> 00:12:55,562
But she blocks the oven and she says, "I'm the
lead singer, and it's done when I say it's done."

108
00:12:55,672 --> 00:12:58,505
So I don't know what to do.
The Supremes are having a fight in my kitchen.

109
00:12:58,608 --> 00:13:01,509
- But then suddenly we hear...
- Hey.

110
00:13:01,611 --> 00:13:04,205
Ain't you Terence Ray's little girl?

111
00:13:04,314 --> 00:13:06,714
Yes, sir. Lily.

112
00:13:06,817 --> 00:13:09,718
<i>Daddy know you out here with her?</i>

113
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:12,880
Rosaleen works for us.

114
00:13:12,989 --> 00:13:16,322
Whole lot of niggers been
coming through here today.

115
00:13:16,426 --> 00:13:18,986
You wouldn't be going to
that secret meetin', would ya?

116
00:13:19,095 --> 00:13:22,587
Well, hell, we ain't gotta
worry about this one.

117
00:13:22,699 --> 00:13:25,896
Can't register to vote
if you can't write your own name.

118
00:13:26,002 --> 00:13:30,371
Tell me, Lily. She a smart nigger
or a dumb nigger?

119
00:13:30,473 --> 00:13:32,168
- Please, mister, we really need...
- Answer me, girl.

120
00:13:39,115 --> 00:13:47,352
R-O-S-A-L-E-E-N.

121
00:13:49,092 --> 00:13:51,890
No!

122
00:13:53,163 --> 00:13:55,654
- Rosaleen! Stop!
- Put her there!

123
00:13:57,701 --> 00:14:00,329
Apologize!

124
00:14:00,437 --> 00:14:02,337
<i>Stop! No!</i>

125
00:14:02,439 --> 00:14:05,067
- Apologize!
- <i> Rosaleen, just apologize!</i>

126
00:14:06,309 --> 00:14:08,209
<i>Help! Somebody help!</i>

127
00:14:08,311 --> 00:14:10,211
Quiet.

128
00:14:10,313 --> 00:14:11,871
- Can somebody help?
- Apologize.

129
00:14:11,982 --> 00:14:13,745
Daddy!

130
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,754
Your black ass gonna apologize
one way or the other.

131
00:14:24,661 --> 00:14:27,027
Rosaleen. Rosaleen.

132
00:14:32,202 --> 00:14:34,363
- Thank you, Sheriff.
- You have to help her.

133
00:14:34,471 --> 00:14:36,200
- <i> Get in the goddamn truck.</i>
- <i>I ain't restin;...</i>

134
00:14:36,306 --> 00:14:38,274
- till your nigger apologizes.
- I'm sorry, Frank!

135
00:14:38,375 --> 00:14:42,402
- I promised her!
- Get in the goddamn truck.

136
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:46,449
She dumped snuff juice
on a white man...

137
00:14:46,549 --> 00:14:49,143
on Frank Posey, for Christ's sake.

138
00:14:49,252 --> 00:14:52,585
I wouldn't be surprised
if he flat-out kills her.

139
00:14:52,689 --> 00:14:57,456
You don't mean that.
He wouldn't really kill her.

140
00:14:57,560 --> 00:15:00,893
Sheriff s gonna take her to the hospital.
She'll be fine.

141
00:15:00,997 --> 00:15:03,488
Goddamn it. What the hell
were you thinkin'?

142
00:15:18,014 --> 00:15:20,312
Don't you leave this room, you hear?
I gotta settle payroll with...

143
00:15:20,417 --> 00:15:22,681
You don't scare me.

144
00:15:22,786 --> 00:15:25,254
- What'd you say?
- You're a coward.

145
00:15:27,254 --> 00:15:30,815
My mother would never let you touch me!

146
00:15:30,925 --> 00:15:33,519
That goddamn woman
give a shit about you.

147
00:15:33,628 --> 00:15:35,755
She loved me.

148
00:15:35,863 --> 00:15:38,161
I hate you!

149
00:15:47,608 --> 00:15:50,600
<i>Now you listen here.</i>

150
00:15:50,711 --> 00:15:55,546
Truth is, your sorry mama,
she ran off and left you.

151
00:15:57,385 --> 00:16:02,322
<i>On the day she died, she come back</i>
<i>for the rest of her things...not you.</i>

152
00:16:02,423 --> 00:16:04,288
That ain't true.

153
00:16:06,927 --> 00:16:09,327
It's not.

154
00:16:41,228 --> 00:16:43,628
<i>Dr. Cash, please call the page.</i>

155
00:16:43,731 --> 00:16:46,757
<i>Dr. Cash, please call</i>
<i>the page operator.</i>

156
00:16:57,178 --> 00:16:59,612
Rosaleen.

157
00:16:59,714 --> 00:17:01,511
They beat you again?

158
00:17:01,615 --> 00:17:04,948
We gotta get you out of here.

159
00:17:05,052 --> 00:17:08,419
- I can't get out of here. I'm in jail.
- You shouldn't be.

160
00:17:08,522 --> 00:17:10,990
That's gotta go.

161
00:17:17,264 --> 00:17:19,926
Rosaleen.

162
00:17:26,841 --> 00:17:30,208
- This is crazy.
- Oh, it'll be all right.

163
00:17:30,311 --> 00:17:32,108
It'll be all right.

164
00:17:38,052 --> 00:17:40,543
Shh.

165
00:17:55,836 --> 00:17:59,636
- A white girl come by here?
- Uh, no, sir. Nobody. I ain't moved from this spot.

166
00:18:22,096 --> 00:18:25,998
<i>When I was born</i>

167
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:29,558
<i>My daddy said I was broken</i>

168
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:32,639
<i>Beginning of the end</i>

169
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:37,939
- You gals be careful now.
- <i>The life I hadn't chosen</i>

170
00:19:02,636 --> 00:19:04,797
Let me get this straight.

171
00:19:04,905 --> 00:19:07,135
You got us goin' to Tiburon...

172
00:19:07,241 --> 00:19:10,404
'cause your mama got a picture
with that town written on the back?

173
00:19:10,511 --> 00:19:12,536
That's it?

174
00:19:12,646 --> 00:19:14,910
T. Ray said my mother left me
way before she died.

175
00:19:19,687 --> 00:19:22,383
Well, it's not true.

176
00:19:22,489 --> 00:19:24,957
He only made it up to punish me.
I know he did.

177
00:19:25,059 --> 00:19:27,084
Knowing your daddy,
he could do a thing like that.

178
00:19:27,194 --> 00:19:29,856
And my mother could never do
what he said she did.

179
00:19:33,334 --> 00:19:35,234
Huh.

180
00:19:36,337 --> 00:19:38,396
I get it.

181
00:19:38,505 --> 00:19:40,530
You ran off 'cause of
what he said, didn't you?

182
00:19:41,976 --> 00:19:45,207
It ain't had nothin' to do
with me being in jail.

183
00:19:45,312 --> 00:19:50,375
And here you got me worrying myself sick
about you getting in trouble 'cause of me.

184
00:19:50,484 --> 00:19:54,750
So what you fixin' to do? Go door-to-door
askin' folks about your mama?

185
00:19:54,855 --> 00:19:57,346
- That's your bright idea?
- I don't exactly have a plan, all right?

186
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:59,824
Well, you sure had one
back at the hospital.

187
00:19:59,927 --> 00:20:02,691
Comin' in there and sayin',
"We gonna do this, and we gonna do that."

188
00:20:02,796 --> 00:20:06,163
And I'm supposed to follow you
like some dumb nigger like they said.

189
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:08,701
Well, you are dumb pouring your spit
on that man's shoe like that...

190
00:20:08,802 --> 00:20:11,600
and dumber not to say you're sorry
if sayin' it will save your life.

191
00:20:11,705 --> 00:20:13,798
That man was gonna come back
and kill you or worse.

192
00:20:13,908 --> 00:20:17,571
And I go and I get you out of there,
and this is how you thank me?

193
00:20:18,512 --> 00:20:21,003
Well, fine.

194
00:21:01,155 --> 00:21:03,055
Are you all right?

195
00:21:04,391 --> 00:21:06,484
I feel like I've been beaten
with a stick.

196
00:21:06,593 --> 00:21:08,857
You have been beaten, remember?

197
00:21:08,963 --> 00:21:11,761
But not with a stick.

198
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:23,169
I know you can't understand.

199
00:21:23,277 --> 00:21:27,680
Apologizing to those men
would've just been a different way of dyin'...

200
00:21:27,781 --> 00:21:30,011
'cept I have to live with it.

201
00:21:33,954 --> 00:21:37,856
If I can find someplace open,
I'll buy us some food.

202
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:40,119
What we gonna do for beds?

203
00:21:40,227 --> 00:21:42,559
Find a motel, I guess.

204
00:21:42,663 --> 00:21:45,757
Lily, there ain't gonna be a place
that'll take a colored woman.

205
00:21:45,866 --> 00:21:47,857
Well, what about
the Civil Rights Act?

206
00:21:50,004 --> 00:21:52,495
Ain't nothin' but a piece of paper.

207
00:22:02,616 --> 00:22:05,949
Excuse me, sir.
Are you serving food today?

208
00:22:06,053 --> 00:22:09,887
Oh, yes, ma'am. We have
a Sunday plate special: Barbecued pork.

209
00:22:09,990 --> 00:22:12,481
Um, we'll take two of those,
please, and two Cokes.

210
00:22:15,295 --> 00:22:16,887
I don't believe
I've seen you before.

211
00:22:16,997 --> 00:22:19,932
I'm not from here.
I'm... I'm just visiting my grandmother.

212
00:22:20,034 --> 00:22:22,366
<i>Your daddy's gonna be so proud of you.</i>

213
00:22:22,469 --> 00:22:24,266
- Afternoon, Carol.
- Hi.

214
00:22:24,371 --> 00:22:25,838
- Why, don't you two look smart.
- When we get home...

215
00:22:25,939 --> 00:22:29,272
You come on in, and I'll wrap
those up for you to go.

216
00:22:43,357 --> 00:22:45,985
Miss, you change your mind?

217
00:22:46,093 --> 00:22:49,426
- Where did you get those?
- Oh, I know what you mean.

218
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:52,055
<i>Virgin Mary's pictured</i>
<i>as a colored woman.</i>

219
00:22:52,166 --> 00:22:55,135
<i>But, see, the woman that makes</i>
<i>the honey is colored herself.</i>

220
00:22:55,235 --> 00:22:57,533
Best honey in South Carolina.

221
00:22:57,638 --> 00:22:59,299
What is her name?

222
00:22:59,406 --> 00:23:02,204
August Boatwright.

223
00:23:02,309 --> 00:23:04,402
Do you know where she lives?

224
00:23:04,511 --> 00:23:09,107
Darnedest house you ever saw. Painted like
Pepto-Bismol. Your grandma's probably seen it.

225
00:23:15,122 --> 00:23:16,953
<i>What do you think's goin' on?</i>

226
00:23:17,057 --> 00:23:20,493
Look like they dressed for church.

227
00:23:20,594 --> 00:23:23,154
- Bye-bye!
- <i> You think one of them's August?</i>

228
00:23:23,263 --> 00:23:25,288
Whoever she is, I hope she make honey...

229
00:23:25,399 --> 00:23:27,560
better than she picks out paint.

230
00:23:28,602 --> 00:23:30,832
I like it.

231
00:23:50,390 --> 00:23:53,325
Now, don't go gettin'
your hopes up, all right?

232
00:23:53,427 --> 00:23:55,691
They got nowhere else to go.

233
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:15,043
Yes?

234
00:24:15,149 --> 00:24:18,380
- Are you August Boatwright?
- <i>No.</i>

235
00:24:18,485 --> 00:24:22,444
I'm June Boatwright.
August is my sister.

236
00:24:23,657 --> 00:24:27,525
- You came to see her?
- Hi. I'm May Boatwright.

237
00:24:27,628 --> 00:24:31,086
I'm August's sister too.

238
00:24:31,198 --> 00:24:33,462
Is she expecting you?

239
00:24:33,567 --> 00:24:35,865
Um, I just saw some honey at the store,
and the man said that...

240
00:24:35,969 --> 00:24:37,960
You come for honey?

241
00:24:38,071 --> 00:24:42,371
Why didn't you say so?
Come into the parlor. I'll go get her.

242
00:24:42,476 --> 00:24:45,968
Then after that she gonna go get
September and October.

243
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:28,520
<i>Who we got here?</i>

244
00:25:32,059 --> 00:25:34,687
I'm Lily and this is Rosaleen.

245
00:25:36,863 --> 00:25:39,423
We need a place to stay.

246
00:25:43,136 --> 00:25:46,469
You see, my mother died of tularemia when
I was little, and my daddy just got killed...

247
00:25:46,573 --> 00:25:49,633
in a tractor accident on our farm in
Spartanburg County, so me and Rosaleen...

248
00:25:49,743 --> 00:25:52,769
she's our housekeeper... we're on our way
to Virginia to stay with my Aunt Bernie.

249
00:25:52,879 --> 00:25:55,211
'Cept I don't have money
for a train ticket or a motel...

250
00:25:55,315 --> 00:25:57,340
and not that anyone
would take in a Negro woman...

251
