and they'd have to call the police.

285
00:28:36,943 --> 00:28:41,573
I feel like I'm where I'm supposed to be.
I really do.

286
00:28:41,681 --> 00:28:46,482
I just need some time to figure out why,
so don't say anything.

287
00:28:46,586 --> 00:28:49,646
Your secret.
You do what you want with it.

288
00:28:52,092 --> 00:28:54,322
They're so cultured.

289
00:28:56,229 --> 00:28:58,254
I never met Negro women
like them before.

290
00:28:58,365 --> 00:29:02,392
- Just us dumb ignorant ones.
- That's not what I'm sayin'.

291
00:29:06,206 --> 00:29:08,731
Guess I never met Negro women
like them neither.

292
00:29:08,842 --> 00:29:12,403
- How much land did she say they got?
- Twenty-eight acres.

293
00:29:12,512 --> 00:29:16,881
It's like it's got its own spot in the world,
where the outside don't come in.

294
00:29:16,983 --> 00:29:18,814
<i>Well, that's a good thing.</i>

295
00:29:18,919 --> 00:29:21,285
We'll be safe here, right?

296
00:29:37,571 --> 00:29:39,471
<i>This is bullshit.</i>

297
00:29:39,573 --> 00:29:41,564
You know she in
some kind of trouble.

298
00:29:41,675 --> 00:29:44,337
Well, who's gonna
take 'em in if we don't?

299
00:29:44,444 --> 00:29:47,140
No one around here.

300
00:29:47,247 --> 00:29:49,477
So what if that trouble follow 'em?

301
00:29:53,286 --> 00:29:55,652
I need to do this, all right?

302
00:30:22,349 --> 00:30:27,446
<i>I went down to the water</i>

303
