348
00:33:42,549 --> 00:33:44,915
<i>Mmm.</i>

349
00:33:45,018 --> 00:33:48,181
How come y'all got names
from a calendar?

350
00:33:48,288 --> 00:33:50,017
Our mama loved spring and summer.

351
00:33:52,959 --> 00:33:56,895
We had an April too, but...

352
00:33:58,231 --> 00:34:00,699
she died when she was little.

353
00:34:10,844 --> 00:34:13,540
- You ain't gonna fix that car.
- I'm gonna fix it.

354
00:34:17,751 --> 00:34:20,219
- What set May off?

355
00:34:20,320 --> 00:34:22,948
She upset 'cause
you won't marry Neil.

356
00:34:24,858 --> 00:34:27,486
See that? You should go on and marry me
and quit upsettin' your sister.

357
00:34:27,594 --> 00:34:29,789
Get out of here.

358
00:34:29,896 --> 00:34:32,626
No, woman, you promised me pancakes,
and I ain't leavin' till I get 'em.

359
00:34:32,732 --> 00:34:36,259
You must be Rosaleen. Neil.

360
00:34:36,369 --> 00:34:37,836
- And you must be Lily.
- Yes, sir.

361
00:34:37,937 --> 00:34:40,963
What's burnin'?

362
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:49,508
Don't worry.
We'll just make you another one.

363
00:34:49,616 --> 00:34:52,141
Or how about some grits?

364
00:34:52,252 --> 00:34:54,846
No. Thank you.
That's... That's all right.

365
00:34:54,954 --> 00:34:56,751
I'm just not really hungry.

366
00:34:56,856 --> 00:34:59,188
Then let's get to work.

367
00:34:59,292 --> 00:35:01,089
Check on May.

368
00:35:01,194 --> 00:35:04,527
I'm going to the N.A.A.C.P. Offices.
We're canvassing voters this morning.

369
00:35:04,631 --> 00:35:06,299
<i>Uh, wait.</i>
<i>What about my pancakes?</i>

370
00:35:06,299 --> 00:35:07,698
<i>Uh, wait.</i>
<i>What about my pancakes?</i>

371
00:35:07,801 --> 00:35:09,462
The batter's right there
by the griddle.

372
00:35:12,772 --> 00:35:15,036
