01:24:14,974 --> 01:24:17,238
- And I killed her.
- Who, Lily?

933
01:24:17,343 --> 01:24:20,642
My mother.
I killed my mother.

934
01:24:22,382 --> 01:24:25,010
I'm unlovable.

935
01:24:31,191 --> 01:24:33,318
Oh, Lily.

936
01:24:34,594 --> 01:24:36,494
You listen to me now.

937
01:24:39,566 --> 01:24:42,467
That's a terrible,
terrible thing for you to live with.

938
01:24:44,003 --> 01:24:47,404
But you're not unlovable, child.

939
01:24:47,507 --> 01:24:49,805
There's love all around you.

940
01:24:53,713 --> 01:24:56,375
Gimme your hand.

941
01:25:03,253 --> 01:25:06,814
<i>I started takin' care of Deborah</i>
<i>when she was nine, back in Virginia.</i>

942
01:25:06,924 --> 01:25:08,915
<i>Over seven years.</i>

943
01:25:09,026 --> 01:25:12,962
<i>Till my grandmama died</i>
<i>and left me this place.</i>

944
01:25:13,063 --> 01:25:16,521
That's why June
resented you at first.

945
01:25:16,633 --> 01:25:20,364
She never got over me
workin' in your mama's house.

946
01:25:20,471 --> 01:25:22,371
How did my mother get down here?

947
01:25:24,475 --> 01:25:28,036
She had an old friend from high school,
moved to Sylvan.

948
01:25:28,145 --> 01:25:32,172
Told her there were jobs,
and men back from the war.

949
01:25:32,282 --> 01:25:34,250
So she moved.

950
01:25:34,351 --> 01:25:36,410
I think it was 'cause of me though.

951
01:25:36,520 --> 01:25:39,284
I just think she wanted me nearby.

952
01:25:39,390 --> 01:25:43,952
So my mother came to Sylvan,
met T. Ray and got married.

953
01:25:44,061 --> 01:25:45,961
That's right.

954
01:25:46,063 --> 01:25:48,122
But what I don't get
is why she married him.

955
01:25:50,000 --> 01:25:54,664
I think Deborah liked the fact
that he was decorated in the war.

956
01:25:54,772 --> 01:25:56,672
She thought he was brave.

957
01:25:56,774 --> 01:25:58,833
Said he treated her like a princess.

958
01:25:58,942 --> 01:26:01,536
It's not the same T. Ray.
I can tell you that right now.

959
01:26:03,747 --> 01:26:07,239
You know, Lily,
people can start out one way...

960
01:26:07,351 --> 01:26:12,516
<i>and by the time life get through with 'em,</i>
<i>end up completely different.</i>

961
01:26:12,623 --> 01:26:16,719
<i>I mean, I don't doubt that he started off</i>
<i>lovin' her. Fact, he worshipped her.</i>

962
01:26:16,827 --> 01:26:22,026
<i>But after about six months or so,</i>
<i>her love wore off.</i>

963
01:26:22,132 --> 01:26:24,396
But she married him?

964
01:26:24,501 --> 01:26:27,902
<i>But if the love had worn off,</i>
<i>why did she marry him?</i>

965
01:26:29,873 --> 01:26:33,365
Honey, Deborah was pregnant.

966
01:26:33,477 --> 01:26:35,377
That's why.

967
01:26:42,252 --> 01:26:44,220
She called me
soon after you were born.

968
01:26:44,321 --> 01:26:48,223
<i>I got letters and phone calls,</i>
<i>mostly about you.</i>

969
01:26:48,325 --> 01:26:52,921
How you were sittin' up
and takin' your first steps.

970
01:26:53,030 --> 01:26:55,464
<i>Playin' patty-cake.</i>

971
01:26:56,800 --> 01:27:01,134
<i>But then the letters</i>
<i>start comin' less and less.</i>

972
01:27:01,238 --> 01:27:03,798
And one day she called me up...

973
01:27:03,907 --> 01:27:06,774
and she said she was leavin' T. Ray.

974
01:27:06,877 --> 01:27:09,038
- Thank you.
- Yes, ma'am.

975
01:27:09,146 --> 01:27:12,309
<i> When I picked her up</i>
<i>from the bus station...</i>

976
01:27:12,416 --> 01:27:14,316
<i>she didn't even look like herself.</i>

977
01:27:15,586 --> 01:27:17,486
<i>She had gotten so thin.</i>

978
01:27:17,588 --> 01:27:20,682
I was with her when you picked her up
from the bus station, right?

979
01:27:23,093 --> 01:27:25,027
<i>She brought me along, didn't she?</i>

980
01:27:28,465 --> 01:27:30,831
<i>No. She came by herself, honey.</i>

981
01:27:34,605 --> 01:27:37,335
<i>Why?</i>

982
01:27:37,441 --> 01:27:39,341
Why didn't she bring me?

983
01:27:41,645 --> 01:27:45,342
All I know, Lily,
is she was fallin' apart.

984
01:27:45,449 --> 01:27:47,349
Depressed people do things
they wouldn't ordinarily do.

985
01:27:47,451 --> 01:27:50,818
It was easy for her to leave me
'cause she never wanted me in the first place.

986
01:27:50,921 --> 01:27:52,821
Lily.

987
01:27:54,892 --> 01:27:57,725
<i>After she was here</i>
<i>for a few months...</i>

988
01:27:57,828 --> 01:28:01,525
and started feelin' better, she...
she start talkin' about how much she missed you.

989
01:28:03,467 --> 01:28:05,697
Then she went back
to Sylvan to see you.

990
01:28:06,803 --> 01:28:09,397
She was just comin' for her things.

991
01:28:09,506 --> 01:28:13,306
- I believe she came back for you.
- I'm goin' to bed.

992
01:28:13,410 --> 01:28:14,900
<i>Lily!</i>

993
01:28:15,012 --> 01:28:18,140
Now your mama
made a terrible mistake.

994
01:28:18,248 --> 01:28:20,148
But I believe she tried to fix it.

995
01:28:20,250 --> 01:28:22,150
Good night.

996
01:28:27,257 --> 01:28:30,055
Damn it, Deborah.

997
01:28:43,340 --> 01:28:44,898
I hate you!

998
01:28:45,008 --> 01:28:47,602
I hate your guts!

999
01:29:06,396 --> 01:29:08,864
Why didn't you love me?

1000
01:30:19,403 --> 01:30:21,303
Tiburon.

1001
01:30:25,075 --> 01:30:26,975
Lily.

1002
01:30:30,781 --> 01:30:33,011
What in Mary's name happened here?

1003
01:30:37,654 --> 01:30:39,554
Answer me.

1004
01:30:47,030 --> 01:30:49,521
T. Ray was right about my mother.

1005
01:30:51,768 --> 01:30:53,668
She left me.

1006
01:30:59,576 --> 01:31:02,238
<i>Hi.</i>

1007
01:31:02,346 --> 01:31:04,246
Hi.

1008
01:31:04,348 --> 01:31:07,283
I brought some
of your mama's belongings.

1009
01:31:12,482 --> 01:31:16,680
It's just a handful of things your mama left
when she went back to get you.

1010
01:31:19,522 --> 01:31:21,513
Been in this box...

1011
01:31:22,992 --> 01:31:25,187
10 years, I guess.

1012
01:31:27,564 --> 01:31:29,691
You really loved her.

1013
01:31:33,870 --> 01:31:37,271
It was complicated.
But, yes, I did.

1014
01:31:38,374 --> 01:31:41,275
How was it complicated?

1015
01:31:41,377 --> 01:31:43,709
I was her nanny.

1016
01:31:43,813 --> 01:31:47,044
Things were different
in her world than mine.

1017
01:31:49,752 --> 01:31:53,210
We like to think
that love is pure and limitless.

1018
01:31:53,323 --> 01:31:57,589
But love like that
can't exist in a hateful time.

1019
01:32:00,163 --> 01:32:02,996
But she made me love her anyway.

1020
01:32:05,835 --> 01:32:09,498
There is no perfect love, Lily.

1021
01:32:26,856 --> 01:32:29,188
Your mama's pocket mirror.

1022
01:32:30,860 --> 01:32:35,058
If you look in here,
you see your mama looking back at you.

1023
01:32:56,886 --> 01:32:58,820
Well, I'll be.

1024
01:33:05,294 --> 01:33:08,525
She was wearin' that pin
the day she got here.

1025
01:33:25,148 --> 01:33:27,173
There's just one last thing.

1026
01:34:09,025 --> 01:34:11,516
Hey.

1027
01:34:11,627 --> 01:34:13,595
Hey.

1028
01:34:23,673 --> 01:34:25,766
- What happened to you?
- What about it?

1029
01:34:25,875 --> 01:34:28,241
It changed you, didn't it?

1030
01:34:33,216 --> 01:34:37,585
Sometimes, Lily, l...

1031
01:34:37,687 --> 01:34:39,587
I get so angry.

1032
01:34:40,957 --> 01:34:43,187
I just want to kill somethin'.

1033
01:34:43,292 --> 01:34:46,159
The men that took you...

1034
01:34:46,262 --> 01:34:48,662
they're angry like that too.

1035
01:34:48,765 --> 01:34:50,926
Makes 'em mean.

1036
01:34:53,236 --> 01:34:55,761
You have to promise me, Zach,
that you won't be like them.

1037
01:34:55,872 --> 01:34:58,136
I don't want to.

1038
01:34:58,241 --> 01:35:00,766
Me either.

1039
01:35:26,969 --> 01:35:29,802
No way I'm not
becomin' a lawyer now.

1040
01:35:31,641 --> 01:35:34,769
I'm gonna be one of them drum majors
Dr. King talks about.

1041
01:35:34,877 --> 01:35:37,004
I know you will.

1042
01:35:37,113 --> 01:35:41,982
And... 10, maybe
15 years from now...

1043
01:35:43,252 --> 01:35:45,152
we'll be at your book signin'.

1044
01:36:03,372 --> 01:36:06,466
So don't forget our story, all right?

1045
01:36:08,444 --> 01:36:10,309
I won't.

1046
01:36:21,257 --> 01:36:25,023
<i>I have you know I am now a registered voter.</i>

1047
01:36:25,127 --> 01:36:27,322
- Really?
- I'll be castin' my vote for...

1048
01:36:27,430 --> 01:36:29,364
Lyndon Johnson and Hubert Humphrey.

1049
01:36:35,004 --> 01:36:37,165
I love you, Miss Rosaleen.

1050
01:36:51,487 --> 01:36:54,217
- Neil.
- Hello, ladies.

1051
01:37:12,508 --> 01:37:14,373
Hi.

1052
01:37:14,477 --> 01:37:17,344
Hi.

1053
01:37:17,446 --> 01:37:21,382
Didn't you call me here to talk?
I'm a little busy.

1054
01:37:21,484 --> 01:37:23,401
You ain't the only one busy.

1055
01:37:23,402 --> 01:37:25,318
I'm just supposed to stand
here and watch how busy you are?

1056
01:37:25,421 --> 01:37:26,752
No.

1057
01:37:34,397 --> 01:37:37,332
I was...

1058
01:37:41,404 --> 01:37:44,271
I was wonderin' if you'd be
willin' to ask again.

1059
01:37:44,373 --> 01:37:46,568
Ask what?

1060
01:37:49,979 --> 01:37:52,072
This supposed to be funny?

1061
01:38:02,191 --> 01:38:04,819
June Boatwright, will you marry me?

1062
01:38:09,699 --> 01:38:11,599
Yes.

1063
01:38:11,701 --> 01:38:13,794
Yes?

1064
01:38:15,071 --> 01:38:16,971
Yes? Yes?

1065
01:38:17,073 --> 01:38:19,701
Yes.

1066
01:38:23,446 --> 01:38:26,540
She said yes.

1067
01:38:26,649 --> 01:38:28,810
- Oh, my God.
- Good for you.

1068
01:38:28,918 --> 01:38:30,909
Come on. We're goin' to
the jewelry store right now...

1069
01:38:31,020 --> 01:38:33,181
pickin' out a ring before you
change your mind, all right?

1070
01:38:33,289 --> 01:38:35,416
What? You don't already have one?

1071
01:38:35,524 --> 01:38:37,424
Girl, come on.

1072
01:38:37,526 --> 01:38:39,790
How come you don't have one?

1073
01:39:08,224 --> 01:39:11,682
Well, well, well.
Look who's here.

1074
01:39:14,530 --> 01:39:16,521
Won't you come in?

1075
01:39:22,838 --> 01:39:25,068
<i>Well, all right, goddamn it.</i>

1076
01:39:25,174 --> 01:39:28,940
<i>You wanna pretend</i>
<i>I'm making a social visit, we'll pretend.</i>

1077
01:39:29,045 --> 01:39:31,843
I'm gonna take you out of here nice and quiet
or kickin' and screamin'.

1078
01:39:31,947 --> 01:39:34,006
<i>Don't matter which one to me.</i>

1079
01:39:34,116 --> 01:39:36,084
Have a seat if you want to.

1080
01:39:49,765 --> 01:39:51,790
So you been here the whole time?

1081
01:39:53,002 --> 01:39:54,902
With colored women?

1082
01:39:55,004 --> 01:39:58,030
- <i>Jesus Christ.</i>
- How'd you find me?

1083
01:40:00,709 --> 01:40:03,439
That map on your wall.

1084
01:40:03,546 --> 01:40:05,707
Came here, started askin' around.

1085
01:40:05,815 --> 01:40:10,081
Some old lady secretary at the law office
was more than happy to fill me in.

1086
01:40:13,556 --> 01:40:16,889
- Where's Rosaleen?
- She took off a long time ago.

1087
01:40:35,377 --> 01:40:38,710
Where'd you get that?

1088
01:40:38,814 --> 01:40:41,112
- Miss August gave it to me.
- Don't you lie to me.

1089
01:40:42,218 --> 01:40:44,118
I'm not lyin'.

1090
01:40:44,220 --> 01:40:46,654
She said it belonged to my...

1091
01:40:49,892 --> 01:40:53,328
I gave that pin to your mama
on her 22nd birthday.

1092
01:40:55,297 --> 01:40:58,095
Now you tell me right now.

1093
01:40:58,200 --> 01:41:00,862
- How'd this August woman get it?
- You gave this to my mother?

1094
01:41:00,970 --> 01:41:02,938
- Answer me.
- You did?

1095
01:41:05,541 --> 01:41:08,533
This is where my mother came
when she ran away from us.

1096
01:41:09,678 --> 01:41:11,873
She was wearin' it
the day she got here.

1097
01:41:22,758 --> 01:41:25,852
Miss August used to take care of her
when she was a little girl.

1098
01:41:36,105 --> 01:41:38,835
I looked for her
everywhere I could think.

1099
01:41:40,943 --> 01:41:42,877
And she was right here.

1100
01:41:44,413 --> 01:41:46,881
Jesus Christ, she was right here.

1101
01:41:59,428 --> 01:42:02,261
Goddamn you, Deborah!

1102
01:42:02,364 --> 01:42:04,229
You ain't leavin' me again!

1103
01:42:04,333 --> 01:42:06,198
Get back here!

1104
01:42:06,302 --> 01:42:08,497
T. Ray, it's me, Lily!

1105
01:42:08,604 --> 01:42:10,595
Daddy!

1106
01:42:26,088 --> 01:42:29,148
You... You look like her.

1107
01:42:37,466 --> 01:42:40,731
My whole life's
been nothin' but a hole...

1108
01:42:40,836 --> 01:42:43,669
where my mother should've been.

1109
01:42:43,772 --> 01:42:45,967
It left me always achin'.

1110
01:42:48,077 --> 01:42:50,272
But I never thought about
what it did to you.

1111
01:42:59,355 --> 01:43:01,949
- We're goin' home.
- I'm stayin' here.

1112
01:43:05,227 --> 01:43:07,991
<i>You think I'm gonna</i>
<i>walk out of here and leave you?</i>

1113
01:43:08,097 --> 01:43:10,088
I don't even know these damn people.

1114
01:43:10,199 --> 01:43:12,099
I know them.

1115
01:43:13,269 --> 01:43:15,396
And August Boatwright
is a good person.

1116
01:43:15,504 --> 01:43:18,234
<i>Now, what makes you think</i>
<i>she'd even want you here?</i>

1117
01:43:18,340 --> 01:43:21,571
Lily can have a home here
as long as she wants.

1118
01:43:24,980 --> 01:43:26,845
Lily said you'd run off.

1119
01:43:26,949 --> 01:43:29,349
Well, I guess I'm back now.

1120
01:43:29,451 --> 01:43:33,911
<i>Well, I don't really care</i>
<i>where you end up...</i>

1121
01:43:35,124 --> 01:43:37,058
but Lily's comin' with me.

1122
01:43:45,100 --> 01:43:47,000
Everybody all right?

1123
01:43:48,570 --> 01:43:50,538
We all right.

1124
01:43:50,639 --> 01:43:52,664
This is Mr. Owens...

1125
01:43:52,775 --> 01:43:54,675
Lily's father.

1126
01:43:54,777 --> 01:43:57,268
He came here for a visit.

1127
01:44:00,449 --> 01:44:02,849
<i>Mr. Owens...</i>

1128
01:44:02,951 --> 01:44:07,888
you'd be doing Lily and us
a big favor by leavin' her here.

1129
01:44:07,990 --> 01:44:11,949
I made her my apprentice beekeeper.
She learnin' the whole business.

1130
01:44:14,997 --> 01:44:16,862
We love Lily.

1131
01:44:18,634 --> 01:44:21,535
<i>We'll get her started in school.</i>

1132
01:44:21,637 --> 01:44:24,970
We'll take care of her.
I promise you that.

1133
01:44:34,083 --> 01:44:36,142
Well...

1134
01:44:38,520 --> 01:44:40,420
good riddance.

1135
01:45:09,218 --> 01:45:11,914
<i>Stop! Stop!</i>

1136
01:45:16,792 --> 01:45:20,728
The day my mother died, you said
she was only comin' back for her things.

1137
01:45:22,131 --> 01:45:24,258
Is that true?

1138
01:45:27,102 --> 01:45:29,002
No.

1139
01:45:30,439 --> 01:45:32,964
No. She was comin' for you.

1140
01:45:36,845 --> 01:45:38,938
Why did you lie?

1141
01:45:42,317 --> 01:45:44,512
'Cause she didn't come for me.

1142
01:46:20,389 --> 01:46:24,382
<i> I still tell myself</i>
<i>that when T. Ray drove away that day...</i>

1143
01:46:24,493 --> 01:46:27,621
<i>he wasn't sayin: "Good riddance."</i>

1144
01:46:27,729 --> 01:46:32,826
<i>He was sayin: "Lily, you are better off there</i>
<i>with all these mothers. "

1145
01:46:34,203 --> 01:46:38,469
<i>I have more mothers than</i>
<i>any three girls off the street.</i>

1146
01:46:39,775 --> 01:46:41,970
<i>They are the moons</i>
<i>shinin' over me.</i>

1147
01:46:48,016 --> 01:46:50,246
<i>I guess I have forgiven myself.</i>

1148
01:46:50,352 --> 01:46:55,153
<i>Although sometimes in the night,</i>
<i>my dreams will take me back to sadness...</i>

1149
01:46:55,257 --> 01:46:59,057
<i>and I have to wake up and forgive again.</i>

1150
01:46:59,161 --> 01:47:02,187
<i>But Mary is always there.</i>

1151
01:47:03,665 --> 01:47:06,133
<i>I feel her at unexpected moments.</i>

1152
01:47:07,503 --> 01:47:09,698
<i>She will suddenly rise.</i>

1153
01:47:09,805 --> 01:47:14,640
<i>And when she does,</i>
<i>she does not go up into the sky...</i>

1154
01:47:14,743 --> 01:47:17,109
<i>but further inside of me.</i>

1155
01:48:15,470 --> 01:48:19,930
<i>If you think</i>
<i>the sky is falling</i>

1156
01:48:20,042 --> 01:48:23,136
<i>Comin' undone</i>

1157
01:48:23,245 --> 01:48:24,803
<i>Hmm</i>

1158
01:48:24,913 --> 01:48:29,373
<i>All the pieces crumble</i>

1159
01:48:29,484 --> 01:48:32,120
<i>You're on the run</i>

1160
01:48:34,356 --> 01:48:38,986
<i>All the wrong you've taken</i>

1161
01:48:39,094 --> 01:48:43,656
<i>All the rules</i>
<i>you're breakin'</i>

1162
01:48:43,765 --> 01:48:48,168
<i>Don't you know</i>
<i>the solid truth is</i>

1163
01:48:48,270 --> 01:48:50,704
<i>It comes back to you</i>

1164
01:48:50,806 --> 01:48:55,436
<i>Don't you know</i>
<i>the sky is blue</i>

1165
01:48:55,544 --> 01:49:00,174
<i>Can't you see the sun</i>
<i>is breakin' through</i>

1166
01:49:00,282 --> 01:49:04,776
<i>Have a little faith in you</i>

1167
01:49:04,886 --> 01:49:10,324
<i>Don't you know</i>
